Fully submerge the @skewers{10} in water and leave them there. Boil a large #pot{} of water with @salt{1%tsp} for your potatoes.

Peel and finely dice the @red onion{1}(peeled and finely diced) and the @garlic cloves{2}(minced). Roughly chop up the fresh @coriander{5}(roughly chopped). Cut any of the larger new potatoes in half. Chop your @British chicken thighs{6}(cut into bite-sized pieces).

Mix the chicken in a #bowl{} with the @smoked paprika{2}. Season with @salt{1/2%tsp} and a few grinds of @black pepper{a few grinds}. Add the garlic, 3 tbsp of the red onion and the zest and juice of the whole @lime{1}. Finally, mix in @olive oil{2%tbsp} and 4 tbsp of coriander.

Boil your @new potatoes{700%g} for around ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Tip: The potatoes are ready once you can easily slip a knife through them.

Drain and keep to the side once ready.

Turn your #grill{} to high heat. Remove the skewers from the water.

> Once the chicken has marinated for at least 10 mins, get the kids to carefully thread the chicken pieces onto the skewers.

Place the skewers on a #baking tray{} under the grill on the highest shelf. Grill them for around ~{10%minutes}, turning occasionally. The chicken is cooked when thoroughly browned off and no longer pink in the middle.

Drain your @organic sweetcorn{1} and mix it with the potatoes and @baby spinach{1} in a bowl. Scatter over 2 tbsp of chopped coriander and mix in 2 tbsp diced red onion.

> Drizzle over 1 1/2 tbsp of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Serve the potato and corn salad with a dollop of @sour cream{6} on top. Lay the skewers on the side and get stuck in!